---
title: Sweet Heat Chicken Cauli Bowls with Cabbage-Carrot Rice & Pickled Cucumber
description: Saucy cauliflower is the star of this bowl, making it a perfect vegan dinner idea! Here, you’ll roast florets until crisp and golden, then coat them in a jammy, garlicky sweet-hot glaze. Nestle the saucy cauli over a steaming bowl of veggie-loaded rice with tangy pickled cukes on the side. This bowl’s got all the bold flavors you crave, without the meat: Witness the power of cauliflower!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-heat-vegan-cauli-bowls-1245db3e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64ef7d9cb6b5b459c56f58b4.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 19 g
  saturated fat: 3.5 g
  carbohydrates: 91 g
  sugar: 35 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1270 mg
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-heat-chicken-cauli-bowls-64ef7d9cb6b5b459c56f58b4
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Cut @cauliflower florets{10%oz} into bite-size pieces. Trim @scallions{2}; mince whites and slice greens on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside to pickle.

> For 4 servings, use ½ tsp sugar.

Open package of @chicken breast{10%oz}(chopped) and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{6%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #large pan{} for 4 servings). Add chicken and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion greens; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}; cook, stirring occasionally, until scallions are slightly charred and veggies are tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

In a second small bowl, whisk together half the @cornstarch{1%tbsp} and ¼ cup cold water (all the cornstarch and ½ cup cold water for 4 servings) until no lumps remain. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium heat. Add ginger and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @apricot jam{1}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, cornstarch mixture, and as much @sriracha{1%tsp} as you like. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and syrupy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce heat to low.

> TIP: Add water a splash at a time if sauce seems too thick.

When cauliflower is done roasting, add to pan with sauce; stir until thoroughly coated.

Stir chicken into sauce along with cauliflower.

Stir cabbage mixture into pot with rice.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with saucy cauliflower and pickled cucumber (draining first). Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.